This is fun.Â  The ASSERT() is incorrect, but that's also not the real
issue here.

The real bug is trying to raise #GP in the virtual vmentry path because
of bad control register state.Â  It should trigger a virtual vmexit
reporting VMEXIT_INVALID.

As for the ASSERT(), (v)GIF blocks external interrupts (inc INIT, NMI
and any #MC which can be delayed).Â  It does not block exceptions, so a
#GP ought to be able to be injected like this.


The real issue here is the reuse of the helpers for main `MOV CR`.Â  They
simply don't behave correctly for nested virt.Â 

Unfortunately, this is going to be quite complicated to fix.Â  I have no
idea when I'm going to have enough time to look into this.

~Andrew

